---
import { withBase } from '../../utils/paths';
import DocsLayout from '../../components/docs/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Local-First Data | PrintKeep by BMR Docs"
  description="Local-first data direction for PrintKeep by BMR, including cautious notes about records, backups, exports, and future documentation."
  heading="Local-first data is the current product direction."
  intro="PrintKeep by BMR is being positioned as a local-first desktop app. This page explains the current direction for local data ownership and responsible expectations while implementation details are still in progress."
>
  <section class="docs-section" aria-labelledby="local-first-title">
    <h2 id="local-first-title">What local-first means here</h2>
    <p>
      Local-first means the product direction favors keeping maintenance records on the user&apos;s own desktop environment
      rather than requiring a cloud account for basic record keeping. Exact storage, backup, and export behavior should
      be documented only when implemented and verified.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="docs-section" aria-labelledby="data-expectations-title">
    <h2 id="data-expectations-title">Responsible expectations</h2>
    <ul class="plain-list">
      <li>Users should plan backups for important maintenance records.</li>
      <li>Future documentation should clearly explain where records are stored before public release.</li>
      <li>Export and restore behavior should not be promised until implemented.</li>
      <li>Cloud sync, accounts, and mobile apps are not part of the current website scope.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="docs-section" aria-labelledby="privacy-direction-title">
    <h2 id="privacy-direction-title">Privacy and legal notes</h2>
    <p>
      Full legal pages are intentionally not part of this milestone. Future privacy and terms pages should be added only
      when the product behavior, availability model, support expectations, and legal copy are accurate.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-panel" aria-labelledby="local-next-title">
    <h2 id="local-next-title">Related documentation</h2>
    <ul class="link-list">
      <li><a href={withBase('/docs/getting-started/')}>Return to getting started</a></li>
      <li><a href={withBase('/features/')}>Review local-first feature positioning</a></li>
      <li><a href={withBase('/support/')}>See current support expectations</a></li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
